explanation: The solution uses the concept of Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS) to find the minimum number of operations required to make the array K-increasing. It divides the array into k sub-arrays and calculates the LIS for each sub-array. The difference between the length of the sub-array and the length of the LIS gives the minimum number of operations required for that sub-array. The total minimum number of operations is the sum of the minimum number of operations for all sub-arrays.

